name: 32 MPa Concrete (Standard)
description: Standard structural concrete used for slabs and columns. Most common grade in Australian construction.
technology: Batch plant mixing with Portland cement
notes: Standard grade for most structural applications

name: 40 MPa Concrete (High Strength)
description: High strength concrete for structural elements requiring greater load capacity. Higher cement content.
technology: Batch plant mixing with higher cement ratio
notes: Higher strength grade for heavily loaded elements

name: 50 MPa Concrete (Very High Strength)
description: Very high strength concrete for high-rise buildings and prestressed applications. Maximum cement content.
technology: Specialized batch plant with quality additives
notes: Premium strength grade for demanding applications

name: 32 MPa GPC (Geopolymer Concrete)
description: Revolutionary low-carbon concrete using geopolymer technology. Reduces embodied carbon by 60% compared to standard concrete.
notes: Award-winning low-carbon alternative to OPC concrete

name: Concrete with 30% Recycled Aggregate
description: Concrete incorporating 30% recycled concrete aggregate. Reduces embodied carbon and diverts waste from landfill.
notes: Sustainable alternative using recycled aggregates

name: Reinforcing Steel (Rebar)
description: Virgin steel reinforcing bars for concrete structures. High embodied carbon but essential structural element.
notes: Standard structural reinforcement for concrete

name: Structural Steel Sections (Beams & Columns)
description: Hot-rolled structural steel sections including universal beams and columns. Primary framing material.
notes: Standard structural sections for building frames

name: Recycled Steel (EAF Steel)
description: Electric Arc Furnace steel from 100% scrap. Reduces embodied carbon by 75% compared to virgin steel.
notes: Sustainable steel made entirely from recycled scrap

name: Steel Mesh (Reinforcing Mesh)
description: Welded wire mesh for slab reinforcement. Prefabricated for faster installation.
technology: Wire drawing and electric resistance welding
notes: Standard mesh for concrete slab reinforcement

name: Australian Hardwood (Spotted Gum)
description: Dense structural hardwood with negative embodied carbon. Acts as long-term carbon store.
notes: TIMBER-HW-001

name: Treated Pine Softwood
description: Plantation softwood treated with H3 preservative. Fast-growing renewable resource.
geographic_validity: Plantation pine with H3 CCA treatment
technology: Standard framing timber from sustainable plantations
notes: TIMBER-SW-001

name: Laminated Veneer Lumber (LVL)
description: Engineered structural timber made from bonded veneers. Consistent properties and high strength.
notes: Veneers glued under pressure with phenolic resin

name: Glue-Laminated Timber (Glulam)
description: Large-span structural beams made from laminated timber sections. Replaces steel beams in many applications.
technology: Engineered beams for long spans and feature elements
notes: TIMBER-GLULAM-001

name: Cross-Laminated Timber (CLT)
description: Revolutionary mass timber panels. Enabling mid-rise timber buildings up to 10+ stories.
notes: Cross-laminated softwood panels with structural adhesive
original_id: Game-changing mass timber for mid-rise construction

name: Clay Brick (Extruded)
description: Traditional fired clay brick. High embodied carbon due to kiln firing at 1000C.
technology: Clay extraction and tunnel kiln firing
notes: Standard clay brick for veneer and structural use

name: Concrete Block (Hollow)
description: Hollow concrete masonry units. More sustainable than solid blocks due to less material.
notes: BLOCK-CONC-001

name: AAC Block (Autoclaved Aerated Concrete)
description: Lightweight insulating blocks with good thermal performance. Lower density than standard concrete blocks.
notes: Lightweight insulating masonry blocks

name: Glasswool Batts R2.5
description: Bulk insulation made from recycled glass. Good thermal and acoustic performance.
notes: Standard bulk insulation for walls and ceilings

name: Rockwool R2.5
description: Stone wool insulation with excellent fire resistance. Non-combustible.
geographic_validity: Melted basalt rock spun into fibers
notes: INSUL-ROCK-001

name: Polyester Insulation R2.5
description: Made from recycled PET bottles. No itch factor and good handling.
technology: Sustainable insulation from recycled plastic bottles
notes: INSUL-POLY-001
